captions.text:
I've never actually worn a boot that's like
the Magista.
It actually felt like a sock.
It's all the boots mixed into one.

It was perfect.
It felt like it was made for me.

It feels like, the boot 
is connected to your foot.

Especially with the kind of grip it has on
the front with the Flyknit.

I think the Flyknit gives you grip, especially
when you're kicking the ball.

It hugs your foot. It gives you a much closer
feel to the ball.

People think it's different, but when they
try this, they will change their opinion.
It's a different class of boot.
